author: lgo
msg: ra_serf: Fix Issue #2888. handle abort() when running 'svn blame' on an older
revision of a file that doesn't exist in HEAD.
Support a file that doesn't exist in HEAD: search for the vcc url through the
parent directories of the file.
Support an older revision of a file: skip the request for the 'checked-in'
property to determine the baseline, but instead pass the specified revision in
the 'Label' header on the request for the baseline collection.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/blame.c
(svn_ra_serf__get_file_revs): handle older revisions of files and files not
existing in HEAD.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/property.c
(svn_ra_serf__search_for_base_props): add a new function that will search
for the base props on the specified path, or any of its parent directories.
Note: this mechanism was based on ra_neon's
svn_ra_neon__search_for_starting_props() function.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/ra_serf.h
(svn_ra_serf__search_for_base_props): declare new function.
